    {
      "id": "aa12b03588d1b98d44a3de7bc5a6f375fdd28aad",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-02-07 17:36:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(7 inline comments)\n\nI'd be really happy to see this land, since I've had a very similar patch that I was working on.  Having a struct ost_id instead of the separate id/gr fields makes some of the code cleaner, and this is a good start toward fixing it.\n\nThere is also similar code that uses \"POSTID\" which could be replaced with DOID/POID, but a few places don't have a struct ost_id to work with so can be left until they can be cleaned up in the FID-on-OST world.\n\nFor a follow on patch I'd like to remove the places that use the compat macros like lsm_object_id, lsm_object_seq, lmm_object_id, lmm_object_seq, o_id, o_seq, etc. so that they can just use ost_id and/or FIDs internally.  In many cases, this will replace separate assignments with struct copying.\n\nWith Di's patch to use FID-on-OST, it may even make sense to change lustre_stripe_md to use a struct lu_fid internally instead of ost_id, to avoid the need to convert the FID repeatedly.  I'm still not sure that we have the FID<->ost_id conversion correct throughout the code, since we are still using seq == 0 everywhere, but this will probably fall out as soon as Di's patches are landed.\n\nNeeds to be rebased on master anyway, so including minor fixes...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
